HEADWORD: Sportive
<hw>Sport"ive</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to,
engaged in, or provocative of, sport; gay; frolicsome; playful;
merry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is it I⟦br⟧
That drive thee from the <qex>sportive</qex> court?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sport"ive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sport"ive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sportless</ent>⟦br⟧
